<span id="freeTextContainer8460355353089778918">Excellent introduction to quantum physics. As a &apos;non-science&apos; person, I can&apos;t say I followed everything but enough to give me a solid understanding for what it is and why it&apos;s so mystifying. The &apos;Many Worlds&apos; theory, however, remains deeply unconvincing. I&apos;m grateful that Gribbin caveats this chapter by acknowledging that it is more opinion than the rest of the book, although he does then proceed to continue in the same &apos;this is undeniably true&apos; tone for the rest of the chapter.</span>
  <span id="freeText8460355353089778918" style="display:none">Excellent introduction to quantum physics. As a 'non-science' person, I can't say I followed everything but enough to give me a solid understanding for what it is and why it's so mystifying. The 'Many Worlds' theory, however, remains deeply unconvincing. I'm grateful that Gribbin caveats this chapter by acknowledging that it is more opinion than the rest of the book, although he does then proceed to continue in the same 'this is undeniably true' tone for the rest of the chapter.</span>
