      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cassandra Kay Silva" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cassandra Kay Silva" href="/user/show/2309246-cassandra-kay-silva">Cassandra Kay Silva</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2309246-cassandra-kay-silva?shelf=science">science</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer119993879" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7942249344049336001">I really enjoy history, and if you are looking for a book that gives much about the history of the development of modern Quantum Mechanics this is a wonderful read. It also simplifies many principles to make it more accessible to non mathematical minds such as myself. Besides that I just kind of loved it and you might too. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


