        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3265489485" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15705712567137583217">Incredibly interesting and moderately approachable for someone with zero experience on the subject. Although it takes a lot of initial historical and scientific background from Gribben, it prepares you to really understand in a meaningful way the basics of the quantum world. <br/>When I truly understood some of the underlying ideas here (after re-reading a few sections multiple times) I was truly amazed and was glad to have read this search into the Schrodinger’s Cat problem. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


